  # DINA UI Bruno Collection
  
  This Bruno API collection is organized around the multiple DINA APIs.
  
  ## ðŸš€ Getting Started
  
  At this point, you should have the DINA-API collection imported into the Bruno project. Which is located in the `dina-local-deployment` repo under `/api-client/DINA-API`.
  
  1. Select your environment using the Environment Dropdown menu at the top.
  
  > Only the "DINA Local" environment is provided by default. Other environments can be added by downloading the environment files in the DINA Wiki under the `Bruno Environments` section. 
  > Add these files under /api-client/DINA-API/environments/ in the `dina-local-deployment` repo.
  
  2. Running any request will prompt you to authenticate via OAuth2. Login with your DINA credentials to obtain an access token.
  
  ## ðŸ“‚ Folder Structure
  
  The collection is organized into folders representing the different DINA APIs. Each folder contains additional subfolders for each resource type within that API.
  
  Inside of the resource type folders, you will find individual requests for common operations such as:
  
  - Get All [Entity]s
  - Get [Entity] by ID
  - Create [Entity]
  - Update [Entity]
  - Delete [Entity]
  
  **Example of the folder structure:**
  
  - DINA-API
    - Collection API
      - Collections
        - Get All Collections
        - Get Collection by ID
        - Create Collection
        - Update Collection
        - Delete Collection
      - Material Samples
    - Object Store API
      - Metadata
    - Agent API
      - Agents
      - Organizations
  
  
  ## ðŸ‘¥ Collaboration  
  
  This collection is intended to be a collaborative resource. Feel free to contribute by adding new requests, updating existing ones, or improving the documentation.
  
  Please ensure no sensitive information (like client secrets or personal data) is included in the collection before sharing.
  
